'''Eric Walter Handley''', {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE}} (12 November 1926 – 17 January 2013) was a British classical scholar, noted for his work on the [[Greek comedy|Greek new comic]] poet [[Menander]]. He was Director of the [[Institute of Classical Studies]], [[University of London]] from 1967 to 1984, [[Professor of Greek (University College London)|Professor of Greek]] at [[University College London]] from 1968 to 1984, and [[Regius Professor of Greek (Cambridge)|Regius Professor of Greek]] at the [[University of Cambridge]] from 1984 to 1994.<ref name="obit - Times">{{cite news|title=Professor Eric Handley|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/opinion/obituaries/article3678988.ece|accessdate=26 April 2014|newspaper=The Times|date=6 February 2013}}</ref><ref name="UCL - Tribute to Eric Handley">{{cite web|title=Tribute to Eric Handley|url=https://www.ucl.ac.uk/classics/events/2013-06-26EricHandley|work=Events|publisher=University College London|accessdate=26 April 2014|date=27 June 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427020348/https://www.ucl.ac.uk/classics/events/2013-06-26EricHandley|archivedate=27 April 2014|df=}}</ref>

==Early life==
Handley was born on 12 November 1926.<ref name="obit - Times" /> He grew up in [[Birmingham]].<ref name="Lampada Tradam">{{cite web|last=Handley |first=E. W. |title=Lampada Tradam |url=https://www.trin.cam.ac.uk/show.php?dowid=737 |accessdate=30 April 2014 |format=pdf |date=19 November 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121209091600/http://www.trin.cam.ac.uk/show.php?dowid=737 |archivedate=9 December 2012 |df= }}</ref> He was educated at [[King Edward's School, Birmingham]], having won a scholarship to the [[Independent school (United Kingdom)|independent]] boys school, and then at [[Trinity College, Cambridge]], where he matriculated at the age of sixteen.<ref name="obit - Times" /><ref name="Lampada Tradam" />

== Personal life ==
Handley married [[Carol Handley|Carol Taylor]] on 31 July 1952. She was headmistress of Camden School for Girls (1971–85) and President of the Classical Association (1996–7).

==Honours==
In the [[1983 New Year Honours]], Handley was appointed a [[Commander of the Order of the British Empire]] (CBE) in recognition of his work as Professor of Greek at University College, London.<ref name="LG 49212">{{London Gazette |issue= 49212 |date= 30 December 1982 |pages= 7–8 |supp= y }}</ref>

